'''[[binomial]] [[nomenclature]]'''
#(''biology'') The [[scientific]] method of [[naming]] [[species]] of [[animal]]s and [[plant]]s whereby each one receives a [[Latinized]] name in two parts; the first is the [[genus]], and is [[capitalized]]; the second is some [[specific]] [[epithet]] that describes the species in some way. The genus part is often [[abbreviated]] to its initial letter e.g. ''H. sapiens'' for ''Homo sapiens''